SCseq filter data¶

filterdata can be run with LBatch and bmode to remove genes associated with batch effects. However, that method does not yield any genes. A nother with the VarID workflow is to regress out the batch effect in pruneKnn with regNB. in that case the regNB parameter of the compNoise function needs to be TRUE as well. Additional variables can be regressed out using the regVar variable with a data.frame. The rownames correspond to cell id and columns to values e.g. cell cycle.

In [8]:
sc_1 <- filterdata(sc_1, mintotal = 1500, CGenes = rownames(so_1)[grep("^(mt|Gm\\d)", rownames(so_1))])
sc_2 <- filterdata(sc_2, mintotal = 1500, CGenes = rownames(sc_2)[grep("^(mt|Gm\\d)", rownames(sc_2))])

expdata_1  <- getExpData(sc_1)
expdata_2  <- getExpData(sc_2)

Create variables for regression¶

In [9]:
# Batch
batch_1 <- so_1$sample_name
names(batch_1) <- colnames(so_1)
batch_1 <- batch_1[names(batch_1) %in% colnames(expdata_1)]

batch_2 <- so_2$sample_name
names(batch_2) <- colnames(so_2)
batch_2 <- batch_2[names(batch_2) %in% colnames(expdata_2)]

# Regression variables 
reg_var_1 <- data.frame(pMt_RNA = so_1$pMt_RNA, msCC_diff_RNA = so_1$msCC_diff_RNA) 
rownames(reg_var_1) <- colnames(so_1)
reg_var_1 <- reg_var_1[rownames(reg_var_1) %in% colnames(expdata_1), , drop = FALSE]

reg_var_2 <- data.frame(pMt_RNA = so_2$pMt_RNA, msCC_diff_RNA = so_2$msCC_diff_RNA) 
rownames(reg_var_2) <- colnames(so_2)
reg_var_2 <- reg_var_2[rownames(reg_var_2) %in% colnames(expdata_2), , drop = FALSE]

Prune KNN and compute cluster with transition probabilities¶

In [10]:
res_1   <- pruneKnn(expdata_1, large = TRUE, regNB = TRUE, batch = batch_1, regVar = reg_var_1, knn = 10, alpha = 10, no_cores = 5, seed = 12345)
cl_1    <- graphCluster(res_1, pvalue = 0.01)
probs_1 <- transitionProbs(res_1, cl_1)

res_2   <- pruneKnn(expdata_2, large = TRUE, regNB = TRUE, batch = batch_2, regVar = reg_var_2, knn = 10, alpha = 10, no_cores = 5, seed = 12345)
cl_2    <- graphCluster(res_2, pvalue = 0.01)
probs_2 <- transitionProbs(res_2, cl_2)

Compute noise from corrected variance¶

In [11]:
noise_1 <- compNoise(expdata_1, res_1, regNB = TRUE, batch = batch_1, regVar = reg_var_1, pvalue = 0.01, no_cores = 5)
noise_2 <- compNoise(expdata_2, res_2, regNB = TRUE, batch = batch_2, regVar = reg_var_2, pvalue = 0.01, no_cores = 5)

sc_2 <- updateSC(sc_2, res = res_2, cl = cl_2, noise = noise_2, flo= .1)
